name: Fixes for index out of bounds exceptions
body: Fixes for index out of bounds exceptions in the data manager.

name: Crash fix for when a brick is null, resulting in a resource id of 0x0.
body:
When a brick is null, it would result in a resource id of 0x0 and a ResourceNotFoundException was thrown.  This caused app crashes.

With the new changes, a factory is used to create view holders.  When an exception is thrown, an empty view holder is used.
Add callback for when view attached to window (#32)
